OL,3,CMinister announces MOT exemption for
OL,4,Csome cars to ease backlog
OL,6,FIt comes as part of measures to tackle
OL,7,Fthe MOT backlog and reduce waiting
OL,8,Ftimes for drivers in Northern Ireland.
OL,10,FThe temporary exemptions will apply to
OL,11,Fprivate cars first registered between
OL,12,F1 June 2019 and 31 May 2020, or
OL,13,Fbetween 1 June 2017 and 31 May 2018,
OL,14,Fwhich have a valid MOT certificate.
OL,16,FThey will come into effect from 1 June
OL,17,F2024 and will allow motorists to
OL,18,Fcontinue to legally drive their
OL,19,Fvehicles as long as they are
OL,20,Froadworthy and are taxed and insured.
